ll-1957/" class="external" target="_blank">“The White Negro” by Norman Mailer | <i>Dissent</i>, 1957</a> • <a href="https://pubs.lib.uiowa.edu/iowareview/article/id/20718/" class="external" target="_blank">“Dragon Slayers” by Jerald Walker | <i>The Iowa Review, </i>2006</a> • <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/01/17/opinion/american-fiction-black-satire.html" class="external" target="_blank">“The Hidden Lesson of ‘American Fiction’” by John McWhorter | <i>The New York Times</i></a> • <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pAweg5PaMuw" class="external" target="_blank"><i>Origin </i>(movie) | Official Trailer</a> • <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/annihilation-adaptation-whats-it-really-like-to-have/id1293762863?i=1000403357605" class="external" target="_blank">Fiction/Non/Fiction Season 1, Episode 11, “Annihilation, Adaptation: What&#8217;s It Really Like to Have Your Book Made Into a Movie”</a> • <a href="https://lithub.com/brit-bennett-and-emily-halpern-on-screenwritings-tips-for-fiction/">Fiction/Non/Fiction Season 2, Episode 11, “Brit Bennett and Emily Halpern on Screenwriting’s Tips for Fiction”</a> •<a href="https://lithub.com/the-stakes-of-the-writers-strike-benjamin-percy-on-the-wga-walkout-streaming-and-the-survival-of-screenwriting/">Fiction/Non/Fiction Season 6, Episode 33, “The Stakes of the Writers’ Strike: Benjamin Percy on the WGA Walkout, Streaming, and the Survival of Screenwriting”</a> • <a href="https://lithub.com/jacinda-townsend-on-why-democrats-are-skeptical-of-president-biden-and-how-he-can-win-them-back/">Fiction/Non/Fiction Season 6, Episode 38, “Jacinda Townsend on Why Democrats Are Skeptical of President Biden—and How He Can Win Them Back”</a></p>
